| Uncle Sam Earns C-minus Grade for PC Security                      |
|   from the not-that-important dept.                                |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Thursday April 12, @20:11 (Security)     |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/12/2323232           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "Twenty-four federal departments and agencies
earned [0]a collective grade of C-minus last year for their performance
in meeting computer and network security requirements, according to marks
handed out by a key congressional oversight committee today. The
government-wide grade is up slightly from the 2005, when it earned an
overall grade of D+. Eight agencies earned A grades, while as many
warranted failing marks. '..the Department of Defense led a group of
eight agencies that received failing marks for computer security. Also
receiving that dubious distinction were the departments of Agriculture,
Commerce, Education, Interior, State and Treasury, as well as the Nuclear
Regulatory Commission. The Department of Homeland Security earned a D,
although its overall performance improved since 2005. The Department of
Veterans Affairs did not provide enough data to earn a grade. In 2005, it
received an F.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/12/2323232

Links:
    0. http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/04/12/AR2007041201010.html


