| Massive Spam Shot of "Storm Trojan"                                |
|   from the storm-warning dept.                                     |
|   posted by kdawson on Friday April 13, @11:31 (Spam)              |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/13/1358210           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

jcatcw writes "Postini has already counted nearly [0]5 million copies of
the spam in the last 24 hours, and calculated that the run currently
accounts for 87% of all malware being spread through email. 'Expect this
to grow much larger,' a Postini spokesman said; 'It should top out at 60
million messages within the next 24 hours.' It's the largest attack in
the last 12 months, and more than three times the volume of the two
biggest in recent memory: a pair of blasts in December and [1]January.
The spam carries a ZIP file attachment posing as a patch with subjects
such as Worm Alert!, Worm Detected, Spyware Detected!, or Virus Activity
Detected."

